    {
      "sort": 300000,
      "name": "Roll Dialog",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "8W29zhp0MktAgqbd",
      "system": {},
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>The roll dialog is reactive. This means you can open the roll dialog by clicking on one of the three roll types (e.G. Quick Roll). Now you can (de)select tags &amp; statuses from your character sheet and they will get added or removed from the roll dialog.</p><p></p><p>The same applies for the GM when adding or removing tags &amp; statuses from the scene.</p>"
      },
